headline: Prized free-agent tackle Terron Armstead to visit Dolphins; La’el Collins goes to Bengals
author: Tribune News Service
sentences: The Dolphins are hosting the free-agent cycle’s most prized player at the position in New Orleans Saints left tackle Terron Armstead on Monday after he travels Sunday night, according to a league source and as first reported by NFL Network.
A week-long wait in free agency for the Miami Dolphins to address what is likely the NFL’s most glaring hole at offensive tackle finally is seeing some movement.
